        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-14T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="936" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d936">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5034 Registration/6–1445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-14T16:00:00-04:00">June 14, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>904. In recent meeting with Assistant Secretary Clayton T. V. Soong stated that
                    registration of foreign firms would be postponed for at least a year giving
                    ample time for further conversations. Embassy is requested to make discreet
                    inquiries and if confirmed, report by telegram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
